Kirkland.Overlake Hospital Medical Center:
Overlake Hospital Medical Center is a 349-bed non-profit community hospital located in Bellevue, Washington. The hospital opened in 1960, and operates a level III emergency room.
In the last year with available data, the hospital had about 53,572 emergency room visits, 20,562 in-patient visits, 7,073 in-patient surgeries, and 7,512 outpatient surgeries.
